decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller.     * This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

getMaxAvailable().details: Get the maximum possible option size

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller.     * This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

openPosition(bool,address,uint80,uint256.details: Open a new call or put options.

params.a_: the amount to spend on on the option
params.k_: type of option to buy (true for call )
params.pp_: the address of the price provider to use (must be in the list of aprvd from IAPP)
params.t_: the rounds until your options expiration (must be minT < t_ > maxT)

params.amount_: the amount you want to deposit to be used for underwriting options

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

toggleStaking().details: used to send this pool into EOL mode when a newer one is open

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}.     * Requirements:     * - `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}.     * Requirements:     * - `sender` and `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - `sender` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``sender``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

updateAPP(address).details: set the new address of the Approved Price Providers(APP)

params.newAPP_: the new approved price provider (and ratecalc contract to use). Must be a IAPP

updateBase(uint256).details: set the base amount of the token. important for tokens that have more or less then 18 decimal places

updateMaxT(uint256).details: update the max rounds for an option position

params.newMax_: the new maximum time (in rounds) an option may be created for (inclusive).

updateMinT(uint256).details: update the min rounds for an option position

params.newMin_: the new minimum time (in rounds) an option may be created for (inclusive).

updateOwner(address).details: set the new address to control this contract

updatePoolLockSeconds(uint256).details: update the pool stake lock up time.

params.newLockSeconds_: the new lock time, in seconds

updateProtocolFee(uint256).details: set the fee users pay to buy an option

params.newProtocolFee_: the new fee (in tenth percent) to buy an option

updateSettlerFee(uint256).details: set the fee users can recieve for exercising/expiring other users options

params.fee_: the new fee for exercising/expiring a options

updateTreasury(address).details: set the new address of the treasury that early withdraw fees or protocol fees go to

withdraw(uint256).details: recieve tokens from the pool. If the current time is before your next available withdraw a 1% fee will be applied.

params.amount_: The amount of LP token to return the pool (burn).
